Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock struck a second half-century in succession to help South Africa to a seven-run win over England.
Liam Livingstone and Harry Brook took 52 runs off the next three overs bowled by Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, and Ottneil Baartman.
Kagiso Rabada picked up the wicket of Livingstone and only conceded four runs to see England needing 21 runs off the final two overs.
Aiden Markram took a flying catch with the ball coming over his shoulder to dismiss Harry Brook.
Nortje only conceded six runs in the remaining deliveries to secure the win.
Pre-Game Insights: The difference between the two sides was the innings by De Kock in the Powerplay, according to England skipper Jos Buttler.
Post-Match Reflections: Aiden Markram highlighted the fight spirit of the bowlers and the importance of execution in the final overs.
Jos Buttler admitted that De Kockâ€™s innings was probably the difference in the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Quinton de Kock scored 64 runs off 34 balls in the opening stand with Reeza Hendricks.
David Miller bashed two sixes and four fours in his innings of 43 runs off 28 deliveries.
South Africa scored 63 runs for no loss in the Powerplay and only 35 runs, for the loss of two wickets, off the next seven overs.
